🚚 Core Services

📦

Container Sales

20' and 40' ISO shipping containers in various conditions: Cargo‑Worthy (CW), Wind & Water Tight (WWT), As‑Is, and One‑Trip (new).

🏊

Box Rentals

Short-term and long-term container rentals for temporary storage, events, construction sites, and seasonal needs.

🚛

Delivery & Tilt Placement

Specialized tilt‑bed trailers deliver and place containers precisely on your prepared pad. No crane required for standard placements.

🏗️

Site Assessment

We review access routes, gate widths, turning radius, overhead clearance, and ground conditions to ensure successful delivery.

Who We Are

Container Coalition (Good Stock HQ LLC) is a Service‑Disabled Veteran‑Owned Small Business specializing in ISO shipping container delivery and placement. We serve residential, commercial, government agencies, utilities, and emergency management customers across the Southeast.

🎖️ SDVOSB

Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business verified through VA Center for Verification and Evaluation (CVE). UEI: W8SAGD11LTW8 | CAGE: 15U35

💳 Government Purchase Card (GPC) Accepted

We accept GPC micro‑purchases and Purchase Orders. Quotes use CLIN framework: Container (EA) + Delivery & Placement (EA).

📜 NAICS & PSC Codes

NAICS: 488510 (Freight Transportation Arrangement), 484121 (General Freight Trucking, Long‑Distance, TL), 493110 (General Warehousing & Storage), 541614 (Process/Logistics Consulting), 561210 (Facilities Support), 332311 (Prefab Metal Building/Component), 236220 (Commercial & Institutional Building), 485999 (All Other Transit & Ground Passenger)

PSC: 8145 (Specialized Shipping & Storage Containers), V112 (Motor Freight), R706 (Logistics Support Services), R499 (Support: Professional), V999 (Other Transportation Services), ZZAZ (Other Commercial Items)

💰 CLIN Pricing Framework

Transparent, two‑line structure—easy to compare and award. Request a ZIP‑specific quote.

CLIN Item Unit Notes
0001 ISO Container (20' or 40', new one‑trip or WWT/CW) EA Spec/warranty on request; depot availability by ZIP.
0002 Delivery & Tilt‑Placement EA Level pad & access required; crane if needed quoted as add‑on.

Add‑ons: permits, long driveway/soft ground, escort/crane, weekend/after‑hours.

❓ Frequently Asked Questions

Do you accept Government Purchase Cards (GPC)?

▼

Yes. We accept GPC and Purchase Orders (Net-30). Quotes use CLIN 0001 (Container EA) and CLIN 0002 (Delivery & Placement EA).

What site conditions are required for tilt-placement?

▼

A level, compacted pad with adequate access and overhead clearance. We review gate width, turning radius, and ground conditions; crane is quoted if needed.

Do you offer modifications (doors, windows, insulation, HVAC)?

▼

Yes. We coordinate basic mods and can scope advanced build-outs with partner fabricators. See the Knowledge Hub for planning PDFs.

Can you support disaster activations?

▼

Yes—pre-staging, rapid deployment windows, and documentation for emergency procurement. We align to ICS/NIMS workflows.

What are your delivery areas?

▼

We primarily serve the Southeast: SC, GA, FL, NC, AL, TN, VA, and DC. Contact us for other locations—we can coordinate nationwide delivery through our network.
